#: casca/help_content.py:45
msgid "Two buttons on the home screen, two paths."
msgstr "Zwei Schaltflächen auf dem Startbildschirm, zwei Wege."

#: casca/help_content.py:47
msgid ""
"<strong>Create from preset</strong> — pick an already-cataloged site (Gmail, "
"WhatsApp, Netflix, ChatGPT…), with name, address and icon ready to go."
msgstr ""

#: casca/help_content.py:51
msgid ""
"<strong>Create new web app</strong> — start from scratch: you type in the "
"name and address."
msgstr ""

#: casca/help_content.py:54
msgid ""
"Everything below the name and address is <strong>optional</strong>. Without "
"touching anything, Casca figures it out on its own: fetches the icon, "
"doesn't create a Desktop shortcut, opens in its own window at normal size."
msgstr ""

#: casca/help_content.py:58
msgid "Preset sites"
msgstr "Vorgegebene Websites"

#: casca/help_content.py:60
msgid ""
"A search field at the top filters by site name (<code class=\"eyebrow text-"
"[13px] bg-shell-mist dark:bg-[#2a2836] px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded\">gmail</code>) "
"or by category (<code class=\"eyebrow text-[13px] bg-shell-mist dark:bg-"
"[#2a2836] px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded\">microsoft</code>). Categories start "
"collapsed — tap one to expand it."
msgstr ""

